name: Subak Museum
address: Jl. Gatot Subroto No.5b, Banjar Anyar, Kec. Kediri, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82121, Indonesia
review 1: Detailed study of rice and water politics, harvesting, management. Guided tour. Very detailed. Took about an hour. A bit confusing to drive to.
review 2:
Great place to learns about rise production. Museum includes traditional Balinese family home.
Guide is included in the price.
Great museum for just 15K rp.
Strongly recommended.
review 3: We came here (Jan 2024) but it was closed. Information on Google all said it was open.  Extensive renovations going on. We were told it would be reopening in May. Would advise phoning to check before visiting.
review 4: I had very pleasant experience. It is small exebittion very good guided by passionate staff. Now I get much clearer picture of traditional crop growing and rice terraces has whole new meaning for me. It took me about 30 minutes, and price of 15000idr is fair. I found this gem by chance while waiting for a bus to Java.
review 5: Newly renovated and will be open on the 20th of May 2024 initially for World Water Forum 2024

review 1:
One of the best Betutu Panggang Biang Koripan branches serving delicious Nasi Ayam Betutu accompanied by a Lawar Kecombrang (Wild Ginger) side dish.

Affordable and very popular with both locals and domestic tourists. Plenty of parking for both scooters and cars.

review 4: Chicken dishes cooked with rich Bali spices and herbs. Rich taste, spicy, juicy chicken served with satai lilit and assorted vegetables in affordable price and fair portion. It‚Äôs good place to have lunch or dinner with small group and family. Overall it‚Äôs highly recommended.

name: DINILAKU CAFE
address: Jl. Gatot Subroto, Banjar Anyar, Kec. Kediri, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82121, Indonesia
review 1: Affordable price and nice place to eat.. ah, the coffee tastes good as well. Recommended place.
review 2: We really love the food here and the staff is really great however there's something that's been bothering us about the cleanliness of the place. We saw at least two mice here. I'm not sure if the owner has no idea about their existence hence the lack of action or if they just don't care (maybe the building is old or whatever). One time one mouse even went into the seating area on the second floor. Please do something about it. Thank you.
review 3: Good place with a good coffee!
review 4:
Good place to spend your time with your loved ones.

They have a smoking area without AC and non smoking with AC.

Wide variety of menus with good prices.
review 5: Good place, but no parking space for car
